currentDoc: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

They have been able to focus and build technologies without having to worry about national security.

It is surprising to learn that the United States has progressed far more than other nations in the 50 years. For instance, the United States has successfully built a ship capable of traveling at 1/3 the speed of light. They have been able to focus and build technologies without having to worry about national security.
